{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01YAYuLuB5kcjD33dWqUh8qE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_014yWh2WdgQbVXUjxQY1oBmb","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Phase 1: Sector Rotation Scan","prompt":"You are the Sector Rotation Analyst for a pre-market sector intelligence protocol. Your task is to fetch sector uptrend data from CSV and analyze sector rotation patterns.\n\n1. Fetch the CSV data from this public URL: https://tradermonty.github.io/market-breadth-analysis/market_breadth_data.csv\n2. The CSV has columns for different sectors showing the ratio of stocks above their 200-day MA. Parse the latest row to get uptrend ratios for each sector.\n3. Also fetch sector ETF performance data using yfinance for these ETFs: XLK, XLF, XLV, XLE, XLI, XLC, XLY, XLP, XLU, XLRE, XLB\n   - Get 1-month and 3-month returns\n   - Identify which sectors are in cyclical vs defensive categories\n\nOutput a JSON summary with:\n- Each sector's uptrend_ratio (from CSV)\n- Each sector's 1m and 3m performance\n- rotation_signal (cyclical_leading / defensive_leading / mixed)\n- cycle_positioning assessment\n- uptrend_ratio_overall (average of all sectors)\n\nUse python3 with pandas, yfinance libraries. The working directory is /Users/kavi/Documents/Claude/Projects/AI投資委員會/sector/\n\nReturn the results as a structured JSON block that I can use directly.","model":"sonnet"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2620,"cache_read_input_tokens":48043,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2620},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"75e35f77-da22-4546-82cd-6252b544ace6","uuid":"7b6d1cb7-4091-4f79-b2d1-240386f49f9c"}
