esday, April 21, the U.S. Retail Sales data (for March) will be released at 8:30 AM, along with Business Inventories and Pending Home Sales.\n\nThe CPI release you're looking for was already released earlier in April - U.S. CPI for March was scheduled for Friday, April 10 at 8:30 AM.\n\nSo for this specific week starting April 16, the main retail sales data will be released on Tuesday, April 21, while the week of April 16-17 itself features manufacturing and production indicators rather than the CPI or retail sales figures.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01CrdDqZAnkXDo5ue5gK22ZN","session_id":"75e35f77-da22-4546-82cd-6252b544ace6","uuid":"cd59129e-e6c0-4a6e-9d43-aa2d8876bed7","timestamp":"2026-04-15T16:35:03.380Z"}
