es for the week of April 14, 2026:\n\n## TSMC Q1 2026 Earnings\n\nTSMC reported record-breaking first-quarter revenue of 1.13 trillion new Taiwan dollars ($35.6 billion), beating analyst consensus by a margin that translated to a 35% year-on-year gain. Orders from major clients including Apple and Nvidia have underpinned the strong performance.\n\nMarch 2026 single-month revenue reached NT$415.19 billion, the highest March in TSMC's history with a 45.2% year-over-year increase, reflecting continued ramp of N2 (2-nanometer) production and accelerating AI accelerator orders from customers including Nvidia, AMD, and Apple.\n\nTSMC's Q1'26 earnings conference call is scheduled for April 16, 2026 at 14:00 Taipei time. TSMC is expected to report a net profit of T$542.6 billion ($17.1 billion) for the quarter according to LSEG SmartEstimate.\n\n## Upcoming Earnings Events\n\nTaiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company is scheduled to release its first-quarter 2026 earnings on April 16. The search results did not contain specific earnings dates or reports for NVDA (Nvidia) or AMD (Advanced Micro Devices) for this particular week in April 2026.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01CrdDqZAnkXDo5ue5gK22ZN","session_id":"75e35f77-da22-4546-82cd-6252b544ace6","uuid":"288a072f-9511-4463-8d38-f5a8e2c52f9b","timestamp":"2026-04-15T16:35:05.694Z"}
{"type":"system","subtype":"task_progress","task_id":"af655c0d7454d1df0","tool_use_id":"toolu_014yWh2WdgQbVXUjxQY1oBmb","description":"Running Full sector rotation analysis with CSV + yfinance ETF data","usage":{"total_tokens":16914,"tool_uses":3,"duration_ms":45515},"last_tool_name":"Bash","uuid":"40701f91-a4b4-4de4-962a-6515bbf80fa0","session_id":"75e35f77-da22-4546-82cd-6252b544ace6"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01HvLxmE8xBDMP6pf9a3Xcf9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_012ws1WVTGHdTLCUPYfLmwnD","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cd /Users/kavi/Documents/Claude/Projects/AI投資委員會/sector/ && python3 << 'EOF'\nimport pandas as pd\nimport yfinance as yf\nimport json\nimport urllib.request, ssl\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta\nfrom io import StringIO\nimport numpy as np\nimport warnings\nwarnings.filterwarnings(\"ignore\")\n\nTODAY = datetime.today().date()\n\n# ── 1. Fetch CSV ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nurl = \"https://tradermonty.github.io/market-breadth-analysis/market_breadth_data.csv\"\nctx = ssl.create_default_context()\nctx.check_hostname = False\nctx.verify_mode = ssl.CERT_NONE\nwith urllib.request.urlopen(url, context=ctx) as resp:\n    raw = resp.read().decode(\"utf-8\")\ndf_csv = pd.read_csv(StringIO(raw))\nlatest = df_csv.iloc[-1]\n\n# The CSV provides overall market breadth (Breadth_Index_Raw = S&P 500 stocks above 200MA)\n# There are no per-sector uptrend columns in this CSV; we'll use the overall ratio for\n# \"uptrend_ratio_overall\" and fetch sector ETF data for per-sector approximations.\n\noverall_uptrend_ratio = float(latest[\"Breadth_Index_Raw\"])\nbreadth_date = latest[\"Date\"]\n\n# ── 2. Sector ETF definitions ─────────────────────────────────────────────────\nSECTORS = {\n    \"XLK\":  {\"name\": \"Technology\",          \"category\": \"cyclical\"},\n    \"XLF\":  {\"name\": \"Financials\",          \"category\": \"cyclical\"},\n    \"XLV\":  {\"name\": \"Health Care\",         \"category\": \"defensive\"},\n    \"XLE\":  {\"name\": \"Energy\",              \"category\": \"cyclical\"},\n    \"XLI\":  {\"name\": \"Industrials\",         \"category\": \"cyclical\"},\n    \"XLC\":  {\"name\": \"Communication Svcs\",  \"category\": \"cyclical\"},\n    \"XLY\":  {\"name\": \"Consumer Discret.\",   \"category\": \"cyclical\"},\n    \"XLP\":  {\"name\": \"Consumer Staples\",    \"category\": \"defensive\"},\n    \"XLU\":  {\"name\": \"Utilities\",           \"category\": \"defensive\"},\n    \"XLRE\": {\"name\": \"Real Estate\",         \"category\": \"defensive\"},\n    \"XLB\":  {\"name\": \"Materials\",           \"category\": \"cyclical\"},\n}\n\ntickers = list(SECTORS.keys())\n\n# ── 3. Fetch price history via yfinance ───────────────────────────────────────\nend   = pd.Timestamp.today()\nstart = end - pd.DateOffset(months=4)   # pull a bit extra for buffer\n\nraw_prices = yf.download(tickers, start=start, end=end, auto_adjust=True, progress=False)[\"Close\"]\nraw_prices.dropna(how=\"all\", inplace=True)\n\ndef pct_return(series, days_back):\n    \"\"\"Return percentage change over the last `days_back` trading days.\"\"\"\n    if len(series) < days_back + 1:\n        return None\n    end_price   = series.iloc[-1]\n    start_price = series.iloc[-(days_back + 1)]\n    if start_price == 0 or pd.isna(start_price):\n        return None\n    return round((end_price / start_price - 1) * 100, 2)\n\n# Approximate trading days: 1 month ≈ 21, 3 months ≈ 63\nDAYS_1M = 21\nDAYS_3M = 63\n\n# ── 4. Approximate per-sector uptrend ratio from ETF price vs its own 200MA ──\n# We download 1+ year so we can compute 200-day MA for each ETF\nstart_long = end - pd.DateOffset(years=1, months=1)\nprices_long = yf.download(tickers, start=start_long, end=end, auto_adjust=True, progress=False)[\"Close\"]\nprices_long.dropna(how=\"all\", inplace=True)\n\nsector_data = {}\nfor tkr in tickers:\n    meta = SECTORS[tkr]\n    series_long  = prices_long[tkr].dropna()\n    series_short = raw_prices[tkr].dropna()\n\n    # ETF price vs its own 200-day MA as a proxy for \"uptrend\"\n    if len(series_long) >= 200:\n        ma200 = series_long.rolling(200).mean().iloc[-1]\n        current_price = series_long.iloc[-1]\n        above_200ma = current_price > ma200\n        # Simple ratio: 1.0 if above 200MA, 0.0 if below (single-instrument proxy)\n        uptrend_ratio = 1.0 if above_200ma else 0.0\n    else:\n        uptrend_ratio = None\n\n    r1m = pct_return(series_short, DAYS_1M)\n    r3m = pct_return(series_short, DAYS_3M)\n\n    sector_data[tkr] = {\n        \"name\":          meta[\"name\"],\n        \"category\":      meta[\"category\"],\n        \"uptrend_ratio\": uptrend_ratio,\n        \"return_1m_pct\": r1m,\n        \"return_3m_pct\": r3m,\n    }\n\n# ── 5. Rotation signal logic ──────────────────────────────────────────────────\ncyclical_1m   = [v[\"return_1m_pct\"] for v in sector_data.values() if v[\"category\"] == \"cyclical\"  and v[\"return_1m_pct\"] is not None]\ndefensive_1m  = [v[\"return_1m_pct\"] for v in sector_data.values() if v[\"category\"] == \"defensive\" and v[\"return_1m_pct\"] is not None]\ncyclical_3m   = [v[\"return_3m_pct\"] for v in sector_data.values() if v[\"category\"] == \"cyclical\"  and v[\"return_3m_pct\"] is not None]\ndefensive_3m  = [v[\"return_3m_pct\"] for v in sector_data.values() if v[\"category\"] == \"defensive\" and v[\"return_3m_pct\"] is not None]\n\navg_cyc_1m  = round(np.mean(cyclical_1m),  2) if cyclical_1m  else None\navg_def_1m  = round(np.mean(defensive_1m), 2) if defensive_1m else None\navg_cyc_3m  = round(np.mean(cyclical_3m),  2) if cyclical_3m  else None\navg_def_3m  = round(np.mean(defensive_3m), 2) if defensive_3m else None\n\n# Lead on both timeframes → strong signal; mixed → mixed\ncyc_leads_1m = (avg_cyc_1m is not None and avg_def_1m is not None and avg_cyc_1m > avg_def_1m)\ncyc_leads_3m = (avg_cyc_3m is not None and avg_def_3m is not None and avg_cyc_3m > avg_def_3m)\n\nif cyc_leads_1m and cyc_leads_3m:\n    rotation_signal = \"cyclical_leading\"\nelif (not cyc_leads_1m) and (not cyc_leads_3m):\n    rotation_signal = \"defensive_leading\"\nelse:\n    rotation_signal = \"mixed\"\n\n# ── 6. Cycle positioning ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# Rank sectors by 1-month return (best 3)\nranked_1m = sorted(\n    [(t, d[\"return_1m_pct\"]) for t, d in sector_data.items() if d[\"return_1m_pct\"] is not None],\n    key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True\n)\ntop3_1m  = [t for t, _ in ranked_1m[:3]]\nbot3_1m  = [t for t, _ in ranked_1m[-3:]]\n\ncyclical_top  = sum(1 for t in top3_1m  if SECTORS[t][\"category\"] == \"cyclical\")\ndefensive_top = sum(1 for t in top3_1m  if SECTORS[t][\"category\"] == \"defensive\")\n\nif rotation_signal == \"cyclical_leading\":\n    if overall_uptrend_ratio > 0.60:\n        cycle_positioning = \"early_to_mid_expansion\"\n    else:\n        cycle_positioning = \"recovery_bounce\"\nelif rotation_signal == \"defensive_leading\":\n    if overall_uptrend_ratio < 0.40:\n        cycle_positioning = \"late_contraction_or_recession_risk\"\n    else:\n        cycle_positioning = \"late_cycle_caution\"\nelse:\n    cycle_positioning = \"transition_unclear\"\n\n# ── 7. Build output JSON ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\noutput = {\n    \"generated_at\":            datetime.utcnow().strftime(\"%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ\"),\n    \"breadth_data_date\":       breadth_date,\n    \"uptrend_ratio_overall\":   round(overall_uptrend_ratio, 4),\n    \"breadth_200ma_trend\":     int(latest[\"Breadth_200MA_Trend\"]),\n    \"bearish_signal_200ma\":    bool(latest[\"Bearish_Signal\"]),\n    \"breadth_50_trend\":        int(latest[\"Breadth_50_MA_Trend\"]),\n    \"bearish_signal_50ma\":     bool(latest[\"Bearish_Signal_50\"]),\n    \"rotation_signal\":         rotation_signal,\n    \"cycle_positioning\":       cycle_positioning,\n    \"cyclical_avg_return_1m\":  avg_cyc_1m,\n    \"defensive_avg_return_1m\": avg_def_1m,\n    \"cyclical_avg_return_3m\":  avg_cyc_3m,\n    \"defensive_avg_return_3m\": avg_def_3m,\n    \"top3_sectors_1m\":         [{\"ticker\": t, \"return_1m_pct\": dict(ranked_1m)[t]} for t in top3_1m],\n    \"bot3_sectors_1m\":         [{\"ticker\": t, \"return_1m_pct\": dict(ranked_1m)[t]} for t in bot3_1m],\n    \"sectors\": sector_data,\n}\n\nprint(json.dumps(output, indent=2))\nEOF\n","description":"Full sector rotation analysis with CSV + yfinance ETF data","timeout":120000},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":867,"cache_read_input_tokens":15965,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":867,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":73,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014yWh2WdgQbVXUjxQY1oBmb","session_id":"75e35f77-da22-4546-82cd-6252b544ace6","uuid":"634c8ff5-7160-4e39-89b3-a79b39b10ed8"}
