{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Ba7kF6pJBPebxeJeeKKfd8","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Iran US geopolitical risk stock market April 2026\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Iran War: Ceasefire Offers Relief, Not Resolution | Charles Schwab\",\"url\":\"https://www.schwab.com/learn/story/iran-war-potential-impact-on-global-equities\"},{\"title\":\"Economic impact of the 2026 Iran war - Wikipedia\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Economic_impact_of_the_2026_Iran_war\"},{\"title\":\"Iran Conflict: Oil Price Impacts and Inflation | Morgan Stanley\",\"url\":\"https://www.morganstanley.com/insights/articles/iran-war-oil-inflation-stock-market-2026\"},{\"title\":\"Market Outlook: Stocks fall as Iran talks collapse and oil supply risks rise\",\"url\":\"https://www.bnnbloomberg.ca/investing/market-outlook/2026/04/13/market-outlook-stocks-fall-as-iran-talks-collapse-and-oil-supply-risks-rise/\"},{\"title\":\"Iran and geopolitical risk: Update 2 April 2026\",\"url\":\"https://content.rathbones.com/Rathbones/Iran%20and%20geopolitical%20risk%20update%202%20April%202026%20PDF.PDF\"},{\"title\":\"The 2026 Iran War, An Initial Take and Implications | Oxford Economics\",\"url\":\"https://www.oxfordeconomics.com/resource/the-2026-iran-war-an-initial-take-and-implications/\"},{\"title\":\"Financial Market Commentary | Peter's Stock Market Blog\",\"url\":\"https://looking2thefuture.wordpress.com/2026/04/13/financial-market-commentary-49/\"},{\"title\":\"Iran War Oil Shock: Stock Market Impacts | Morgan Stanley\",\"url\":\"https://www.morganstanley.com/insights/articles/iran-war-oil-shock-stock-market-impacts\"},{\"title\":\"Does war in Iran change the 2026 outlook? | J.P. Morgan Asset Management\",\"url\":\"https://am.jpmorgan.com/us/en/asset-management/per/insights/market-insights/market-updates/on-the-minds-of-investors/does-war-in-iran-change-the-2026-outlook/\"},{\"title\":\"Stock market news for April 13, 2026\",\"url\":\"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/04/12/stock-market-today-live-updates.html\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what's happening with Iran-US geopolitical risk and the stock market in April 2026:\n\n## Recent Developments\n\nMarkets rallied on the U.S. and Iran ceasefire announcement on April 10, 2026, though these moves appear to be driven more by rapid unwinds of hedges and speculative positioning than by a fundamental resolution of the conflict. However, North American markets opened the week lower after U.S.-Iran peace talks ended without a deal, raising concerns about oil supply disruptions and broader economic strain.\n\n## Market Impact\n\nThe conflict has created significant volatility. The 2026 Iran war, including the closure of the Strait of Hormuz, has led to what the International Energy Agency has characterized as the \"largest supply disruption in the history of the global oil market\". Stock markets experienced declines globally and there was a global bonds market sell-off. At the closing lows of the U.S.-Iran war, the S&P was off more than 7% for 2026.\n\n## Economic Risks\n\nMarket volatility is likely to remain high with headline risk driving short-term swings. Rising oil and gasoline prices have reduced the purchasing power of American consumers, with some economists emphasizing that rising oil prices weigh on economic growth and push up inflation.\n\n## Long-term Outlook\n\nHistory suggests equity volatility driven by geopolitics is often temporary, which makes the case against rushed, emotion-driven portfolio shifts. Investors are advised to stay focused on long-term positioning while monitoring geopolitical developments.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01CrdDqZAnkXDo5ue5gK22ZN","session_id":"75e35f77-da22-4546-82cd-6252b544ace6","uuid":"9e21baad-9402-49e5-a099-6872b9aa2307","timestamp":"2026-04-15T16:35:06.505Z"}
