ective structure rather than confirmed new-bull expansion.\n\n**Caution flag:** XLE is a notable outlier — strong 3-month return (+19.64%) but weak 1-month (-2.88%), suggesting energy had a big move earlier but is now rolling over."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: af655c0d7454d1df0 (use SendMessage with to: 'af655c0d7454d1df0' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 22471\ntool_uses: 3\nduration_ms: 68309</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"75e35f77-da22-4546-82cd-6252b544ace6","uuid":"48ecf91d-3bf3-499c-9af8-538101f6b50e","timestamp":"2026-04-15T16:35:28.505Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"You are the Sector Rotation Analyst for a pre-market sector intelligence protocol. Your task is to fetch sector uptrend data from CSV and analyze sector rotation patterns.\n\n1. Fetch the CSV data from this public URL: https://tradermonty.github.io/market-breadth-analysis/market_breadth_data.csv\n2. The CSV has columns for different sectors showing the ratio of stocks above their 200-day MA. Parse the latest row to get uptrend ratios for each sector.\n3. Also fetch sector ETF performance data using yfinance for these ETFs: XLK, XLF, XLV, XLE, XLI, XLC, XLY, XLP, XLU, XLRE, XLB\n   - Get 1-month and 3-month returns\n   - Identify which sectors are in cyclical vs defensive categories\n\nOutput a JSON summary with:\n- Each sector's uptrend_ratio (from CSV)\n- Each sector's 1m and 3m performance\n- rotation_signal (cyclical_leading / defensive_leading / mixed)\n- cycle_positioning assessment\n- uptrend_ratio_overall (average of all sectors)\n\nUse python3 with pandas, yfinance libraries. The working directory is /Users/kavi/Documents/Claude/Projects/AI投資委員會/sector/\n\nReturn the results as a structured JSON block that I can use directly.","agentId":"af655c0d7454d1df0","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is the complete structured JSON result:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"generated_at\": \"2026-04-15T16:35:11Z\",\n  \