{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CrdDqZAnkXDo5ue5gK22ZN","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is the full structured intelligence summary for the sector protocol:\n\n---\n\n## News Catalyst Analyst — Pre-Market Report\n**Date: 2026-04-16 | Pre-Market**\n\n---\n\n## Part 1: Market Sentiment Indicators\n\n| Indicator | Value | Signal |\n|---|---|---|\n| **VIX** | ~18.15 (Apr 15 close; Apr 16 pre-market) | LOW-MODERATE volatility |\n| **Fear & Greed Index** | ~52–58 (Neutral-to-Greed zone, per component inference) | NEUTRAL trending GREED |\n| **Put/Call Ratio (Total)** | 0.68 (Apr 14) | Bullish (below 1.0) |\n| **Put/Call Ratio (Equity)** | 0.50 (Apr 14) | Strongly Bullish |\n| **SPX Put/Call Ratio** | 0.92 (Apr 14) | Near Neutral |\n| **SPY RSI (14)** | 63.83 (Apr 14) | Neutral / Approaching Overbought |\n\n### Derived Composite Scores\n\n```\nfear_greed_index:         ~55  (estimated Neutral/Greed boundary)\nfear_greed_label:         Neutral\nvix_current:              18.15\nput_call_ratio:           0.68 (Total) / 0.50 (Equity)\nspy_rsi:                  63.83\nextreme_sentiment_triggered: FALSE  (neither > 80 nor < 20)\nmarket_regime:            RISK_ON\n```\n\n**Rationale:** VIX at 18.15 is well below the stress threshold of 25. Put/call at 0.68 signals call-side dominance (bullish positioning). SPY RSI at 63.83 is elevated but not overbought. Nasdaq 100 on a 10-session winning streak. Overall regime is RISK_ON with no extreme reading.\n\n---\n\n## Part 2: Top 5 Market Catalysts\n\n### Catalyst 1 — Iran/US Geopolitical Tension: Ceasefire Fragility\n**Impact: NEGATIVE (Binary Risk) | Probability: HIGH within 48h**\n\nThe US-Iran two-week ceasefire is approaching expiration. Peace talks collapsed over the weekend, then tentatively resumed. Trump signaled negotiations could restart \"within two days.\" The US maintains a naval blockade of the Strait of Hormuz; Iran is weighing a temporary halt to shipments. WTI crude is ~$93/bbl, having plunged from peak war-shock levels but remaining elevated.\n\n- **Sectors affected:** Energy (bearish if deal; bullish if collapse), Industrials, Transportation, Airlines, Consumer Discretionary (oil-sensitive), Defense/Aerospace (positive if escalation)\n- **Binary risk within 48h: YES** — Ceasefire lapses imminently; a breakdown or breakthrough will trigger sharp oil price moves and risk-on/risk-off rotation.\n\n---\n\n### Catalyst 2 — Q1 2026 Earnings Season: Broad Beat Momentum\n**Impact: POSITIVE | Ongoing**\n\nS&P 500 Q1 earnings growth tracking +12.5% to +19% YoY — potentially the highest growth rate in 4+ years. Key beats so far:\n- **JPMorgan Chase:** +13% profit YoY ($16.5B), investment banking surging\n- **Citigroup:** Beat on EPS ($3.06 vs $2.65 est) and revenue ($24.63B vs $23.55B est), best quarterly revenue in a decade\n- **Morgan Stanley:** IB revenue +36% YoY on M&A wave\n\n**Today (Apr 16): TSMC Q1 Earnings Conference Call at 14:00 Taipei time**\n- Revenue guided at ~$35.7B (+35% YoY) — record quarter on AI chip demand, N2 ramp\n- Beat would be positive for AI/semiconductor sector broadly (NVDA, AMD, AVGO, LITE, MU)\n\n- **Sectors affected:** Financials (positive), Technology/Semiconductors (positive — TSMC call today), AI infrastructure\n\n---\n\n### Catalyst 3 — Trump Tariffs: Pharmaceutical 100% + China Threat\n**Impact: NEGATIVE for Pharma/Biotech; MIXED broadly**\n\nOn April 2, Trump imposed up to 100% tariffs on patented pharmaceutical imports. Companies without MFN pricing deals face the full rate (effective in 120-180 days). Trump also threatened 50% China tariffs after reports of Beijing arms shipments to Iran. Treasury Secretary Bessent signaled prior tariff levels could be restored by early July via Section 301.\n\n- **Sectors affected:** Biotech/Pharma (negative, especially small/mid-cap), China-exposed Tech, Industrials (steel/aluminum/copper tariffs also active)\n- **Binary risk within 48h: MODERATE** — April 16 is the public comment deadline for manufacturing/forced-labor tariff investigations; potential new announcements possible.\n\n---\n\n### Catalyst 4 — Fed Policy: FOMC on Hold, Next Meeting April 28–29\n**Impact: NEUTRAL | Low near-term binary risk**\n\nThe Fed held rates at 3.50–3.75% at the March 18 meeting. The next FOMC meeting is April 28–29. Market consensus still expects one cut in 2026, one in 2027. March CPI was already released (April 10) — no major inflation print this week. Near-term risk is low; the FOMC meeting 12 days away is the next meaningful catalyst.\n\n- **Sectors affected:** Rate-sensitive sectors (Utilities, REITs, Financials) — NEUTRAL for now\n- **Binary risk within 48h: NONE**\n\n---\n\n### Catalyst 5 — AI Demand Supercycle: Chip Shortage, Agentic AI Boom\n**Impact: POSITIVE | Structural tailwind**\n\nAI accelerator demand is described as creating chip shortages across the supply chain. TSMC's record N2 ramp is driven by Nvidia, AMD, and Apple orders. Q1 S&P 500 Tech sector earnings growth guided at +45% YoY. Nasdaq 100 is on a 10-session winning streak — its longest since 2021. Demand for agentic AI is accelerating beyond data center buildout expectations.\n\n- **Sectors affected:** Semiconductors, Cloud Infrastructure, Data Centers, AI Software, Networking\n- **Binary risk within 48h: YES (positive)** — TSMC earnings call today; a strong beat + raised guidance would act as a sector-wide catalyst\n\n---\n\n### Bonus Catalyst — Oil Shock Overhang / Hormuz Blockade\n**Impact: NEGATIVE (macro drag) | Ongoing**\n\nThe IEA projects global oil demand declining in 2026 for the first time since 2020 as elevated prices curb consumption. US blockade of Iranian oil exports remains active. Oil near $93/bbl is a consumer spending headwind and an inflation risk that complicates Fed dovish pivot expectations.\n\n- **Sectors affected:** Consumer Discretionary (negative), Energy (mixed), Airlines/Logistics (negative), inflation-sensitive sectors\n\n---\n\n## Part 3: Binary Risk Events Within 48 Hours\n\n| Event | Timing | Sectors at Risk | Direction |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Iran ceasefire expiration / new talks | Apr 16–17 | Energy, Defense, Airlines, Global macro | Bi-directional (sharp) |\n| TSMC Q1 earnings call | Apr 16 14:00 TPE (02:00 ET) | Semiconductors, AI infra, NVDA/AMD/AVGO/MU | Likely POSITIVE |\n| Pharma tariff comment deadline | Apr 16 | Biotech/Pharma | Potential negative catalyst |\n| Philly Fed / Industrial Production | Apr 17 | Industrials, Macro | Neutral-to-watch |\n\n---\n\n## Summary JSON for Protocol Handoff\n\n```json\n{\n  \"date\": \"2026-04-16\",\n  \"market_sentiment\": {\n    \"fear_greed_index\": 55,\n    \"fear_greed_label\": \"Neutral\",\n    \"vix_current\": 18.15,\n    \"put_call_ratio\": 0.68,\n    \"spy_rsi\": 63.83,\n    \"extreme_sentiment_triggered\": false,\n    \"market_regime\": \"RISK_ON\"\n  },\n  \"top_catalysts\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"C1\",\n      \"title\": \"Iran/US Ceasefire Fragility\",\n      \"impact\": \"NEGATIVE\",\n      \"binary_risk_48h\": true,\n      \"affected_sectors\": [\"Energy\", \"Defense\", \"Airlines\", \"Consumer Discretionary\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"C2\",\n      \"title\": \"Q1 Earnings Beat Wave + TSMC Call Today\",\n      \"impact\": \"POSITIVE\",\n      \"binary_risk_48h\": true,\n      \"affected_sectors\": [\"Financials\", \"Technology\", \"Semiconductors\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"C3\",\n      \"title\": \"100% Pharma Tariffs + China Tariff Threats\",\n      \"impact\": \"NEGATIVE\",\n      \"binary_risk_48h\": true,\n      \"affected_sectors\": [\"Biotech\", \"Pharma\", \"China-exposed Tech\", \"Industrials\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"C4\",\n      \"title\": \"Fed on Hold, FOMC Apr 28-29\",\n      \"impact\": \"NEUTRAL\",\n      \"binary_risk_48h\": false,\n      \"affected_sectors\": [\"Utilities\", \"REITs\", \"Financials\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"C5\",\n      \"title\": \"AI Demand Supercycle / Chip Shortage\",\n      \"impact\": \"POSITIVE\",\n      \"binary_risk_48h\": true,\n      \"affected_sectors\": [\"Semiconductors\", \"Cloud\", \"AI Infrastructure\", \"Networking\"]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"oil_price_wti\": 93.0,\n  \"macro_notes\": \"Iran ceasefire imminently lapsing is the single highest-impact binary risk. AI/semiconductor earnings cycle is the dominant positive structural driver. Pharma tariffs add sector-specific drag. Fed neutral. Overall regime RISK_ON but with elevated geopolitical tail risk.\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\nSources:\n- [CBOE VIX Historical Data - Yahoo Finance](https://finance.yahoo.com/quote/%5EVIX/)\n- [Fear and Greed Index - CNN Markets](https://www.cnn.com/markets/fear-and-greed)\n- [CBOE Daily Market Statistics](https://www.cboe.com/us/options/market_statistics/daily/)\n- [SPY Technical Analysis - Barchart.com](https://www.barchart.com/etfs-funds/quotes/SPY/technical-analysis)\n- [Stock Market Live April 14, 2026 - 24/7 Wall St.](https://247wallst.com/investing/2026/04/14/stock-market-live-april-14-2026-sp-500-spy-wipes-out-iran-losses/)\n- [Trump threatens 50% tariffs on China - CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/04/13/trump-threatens-50percent-tariffs-on-china-as-report-suggests-plans-for-arms-shipment-to-iran.html)\n- [Trump Tariff Rates Could Be Restored by Early July: Bessent - Bloomberg](https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-04-14/trump-tariff-rates-could-be-restored-by-early-july-bessent)\n- [FOMC March 18, 2026 Statement - Federal Reserve](https://www.federalreserve.gov/newsevents/pressreleases/monetary20260318a.htm)\n- [US Q1 Earnings 2026: S&P 500 Profit Growth 12.5%](https://internationalnewsandviews.com/us-q1-2026-earnings-sp500-growth-banks-results-outlook-401326-2/)\n- [JPMorgan Q1 2026 Blockbuster Results - FinancialContent](https://markets.financialcontent.com/stocks/article/marketminute-2026-4-14-jpmorgan-chase-defies-economic-headwinds-with-blockbuster-q1-2026-results)\n- [TSMC Q1 2026 Earnings: $35.7B Revenue - Techi.com](https://www.techi.com/tsmc-q1-2026-earnings-report/)\n- [Trump's 100% Pharma Tariffs - CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/04/02/trump-pharmaceutical-tariffs-100percent.html)\n- [Oil tumbles below $92 on Iran talks - CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/04/14/oil-wti-brent-as-markets-hormuz-blockade-vance-trump.html)\n- [Iran War Economic Impact - Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Economic_impact_of_the_2026_Iran_war)\n- [Economic Calendar April 2026 - Scotiabank](https://www.scotiabank.com/ca/en/about/economics/economics-publications/post.other-publications.calendar-of-economic-release-dates.calendar-of-economic-release-dates--april-2026-.html)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a1a42566dfdb8255f (use SendMessage with to: 'a1a42566dfdb8255f' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 31837\ntool_uses: 14\nduration_ms: 103505</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"75e35f77-da22-4546-82cd-6252b544ace6","uuid":"0dbfb1a9-7848-4b84-847f-b37634cbe978","timestamp":"2026-04-15T16:36:17.821Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"You are the News Catalyst Analyst for a pre-market sector intelligence protocol (date: 2026-04-16). Your job is to gather real-time market news and sentiment data.\n\nTasks:\n1. Run the market-sentiment-analyzer: use WebSearch to find current VIX level, Fear & Greed index, put/call ratio, and SPY RSI. Search for:\n   - \"VIX index today April 2026\"\n   - \"CNN Fear and Greed index today\"\n   - \"CBOE put call ratio today\"\n   - \"SPY RSI 14 today\"\n\n2. Run market-news-analyst: use WebSearch to find the most impactful market news from the past 3-5 days. Search for:\n   - \"US stock market news today April 16 2026\"\n   - \"FOMC Fed rate decision April 2026\"\n   - \"Trump tariff news today April 2026\"\n   - \"earnings season April 2026 results\"\n   - \"upcoming economic calendar this week April 2026\"\n\n3. Compile at least 5 top catalysts with impact assessment (positive/negative/neutral) and affected sectors.\n\n4. Determine:\n   - fear_greed_index (0-100)\n   - fear_greed_label (Extreme Fear / Fear / Neutral / Greed / Extreme Greed)\n   - vix_current\n   - put_call_ratio (if found)\n   - spy_rsi (if found)\n   - extreme_sentiment_triggered (true if fear_greed > 80 or < 20)\n   - market_regime (RISK_ON / RISK_OFF / VOLATILE)\n\n5. Look for any binary risk events within 48 hours that could impact specific sectors.\n\nReturn a structured summary with all findings.","agentId":"a1a42566dfdb8255f","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is the full structured intelligence summary for the sector protocol:\n\n---\n\n## News Catalyst Analyst — Pre-Market Report\n**Date: 2026-04-16 | Pre-Market**\n\n---\n\n## Part 1: Market Sentiment Indicators\n\n| Indicator | Value | Signal |\n|---|---|---|\n| **VIX** | ~18.15 (Apr 15 close; Apr 16 pre-market) | LOW-MODERATE volatility |\n| **Fear & Greed Index** | ~52–58 (Neutral-to-Greed zone, per component inference) | NEUTRAL trending GREED |\n| **Put/Call Ratio (Total)** | 0.68 (Apr 14) | Bullish (below 1.0) |\n| **Put/Call Ratio (Equity)** | 0.50 (Apr 14) | Strongly Bullish |\n| **SPX Put/Call Ratio** | 0.92 (Apr 14) | Near Neutral |\n| **SPY RSI (14)** | 63.83 (Apr 14) | Neutral / Approaching Overbought |\n\n### Derived Composite Scores\n\n```\nfear_greed_index:         ~55  (estimated Neutral/Greed boundary)\nfear_greed_label:         Neutral\nvix_current:              18.15\nput_call_ratio:           0.68 (Total) / 0.50 (Equity)\nspy_rsi:                  63.83\nextreme_sentiment_triggered: FALSE  (neither > 80 nor < 20)\nmarket_regime:            RISK_ON\n```\n\n**Rationale:** VIX at 18.15 is well below the stress threshold of 25. Put/call at 0.68 signals call-side dominance (bullish positioning). SPY RSI at 63.83 is elevated but not overbought. Nasdaq 100 on a 10-session winning streak. Overall regime is RISK_ON with no extreme reading.\n\n---\n\n## Part 2: Top 5 Market Catalysts\n\n### Catalyst 1 — Iran/US Geopolitical Tension: Ceasefire Fragility\n**Impact: NEGATIVE (Binary Risk) | Probability: HIGH within 48h**\n\nThe US-Iran two-week ceasefire is approaching expiration. Peace talks collapsed over the weekend, then tentatively resumed. Trump signaled negotiations could restart \"within two days.\" The US maintains a naval blockade of the Strait of Hormuz; Iran is weighing a temporary halt to shipments. WTI crude is ~$93/bbl, having plunged from peak war-shock levels but remaining elevated.\n\n- **Sectors affected:** Energy (bearish if deal; bullish if collapse), Industrials, Transportation, Airlines, Consumer Discretionary (oil-sensitive), Defense/Aerospace (positive if escalation)\n- **Binary risk within 48h: YES** — Ceasefire lapses imminently; a breakdown or breakthrough will trigger sharp oil price moves and risk-on/risk-off rotation.\n\n---\n\n### Catalyst 2 — Q1 2026 Earnings Season: Broad Beat Momentum\n**Impact: POSITIVE | Ongoing**\n\nS&P 500 Q1 earnings growth tracking +12.5% to +19% YoY — potentially the highest growth rate in 4+ years. Key beats so far:\n- **JPMorgan Chase:** +13% profit YoY ($16.5B), investment banking surging\n- **Citigroup:** Beat on EPS ($3.06 vs $2.65 est) and revenue ($24.63B vs $23.55B est), best quarterly revenue in a decade\n- **Morgan Stanley:** IB revenue +36% YoY on M&A wave\n\n**Today (Apr 16): TSMC Q1 Earnings Conference Call at 14:00 Taipei time**\n- Revenue guided at ~$35.7B (+35% YoY) — record quarter on AI chip demand, N2 ramp\n- Beat would be positive for AI/semiconductor sector broadly (NVDA, AMD, AVGO, LITE, MU)\n\n- **Sectors affected:** Financials (positive), Technology/Semiconductors (positive — TSMC call today), AI infrastructure\n\n---\n\n### Catalyst 3 — Trump Tariffs: Pharmaceutical 100% + China Threat\n**Impact: NEGATIVE for Pharma/Biotech; MIXED broadly**\n\nOn April 2, Trump imposed up to 100% tariffs on patented pharmaceutical imports. Companies without MFN pricing deals face the full rate (effective in 120-180 days). Trump also threatened 50% China tariffs after reports of Beijing arms shipments to Iran. Treasury Secretary Bessent signaled prior tariff levels could be restored by early July via Section 301.\n\n- **Sectors affected:** Biotech/Pharma (negative, especially small/mid-cap), China-exposed Tech, Industrials (steel/aluminum/copper tariffs also active)\n- **Binary risk within 48h: MODERATE** — April 16 is the public comment deadline for manufacturing/forced-labor tariff investigations; potential new announcements possible.\n\n---\n\n### Catalyst 4 — Fed Policy: FOMC on Hold, Next Meeting April 28–29\n**Impact: NEUTRAL | Low near-term binary risk**\n\nThe Fed held rates at 3.50–3.75% at the March 18 meeting. The next FOMC meeting is April 28–29. Market consensus still expects one cut in 2026, one in 2027. March CPI was already released (April 10) — no major inflation print this week. Near-term risk is low; the FOMC meeting 12 days away is the next meaningful catalyst.\n\n- **Sectors affected:** Rate-sensitive sectors (Utilities, REITs, Financials) — NEUTRAL for now\n- **Binary risk within 48h: NONE**\n\n---\n\n### Catalyst 5 — AI Demand Supercycle: Chip Shortage, Agentic AI Boom\n**Impact: POSITIVE | Structural tailwind**\n\nAI accelerator demand is described as creating chip shortages across the supply chain. TSMC's record N2 ramp is driven by Nvidia, AMD, and Apple orders. Q1 S&P 500 Tech sector earnings growth guided at +45% YoY. Nasdaq 100 is on a 10-session winning streak — its longest since 2021. Demand for agentic AI is accelerating beyond data center buildout expectations.\n\n- **Sectors affected:** Semiconductors, Cloud Infrastructure, Data Centers, AI Software, Networking\n- **Binary risk within 48h: YES (positive)** — TSMC earnings call today; a strong beat + raised guidance would act as a sector-wide catalyst\n\n---\n\n### Bonus Catalyst — Oil Shock Overhang / Hormuz Blockade\n**Impact: NEGATIVE (macro drag) | Ongoing**\n\nThe IEA projects global oil demand declining in 2026 for the first time since 2020 as elevated prices curb consumption. US blockade of Iranian oil exports remains active. Oil near $93/bbl is a consumer spending headwind and an inflation risk that complicates Fed dovish pivot expectations.\n\n- **Sectors affected:** Consumer Discretionary (negative), Energy (mixed), Airlines/Logistics (negative), inflation-sensitive sectors\n\n---\n\n## Part 3: Binary Risk Events Within 48 Hours\n\n| Event | Timing | Sectors at Risk | Direction |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Iran ceasefire expiration / new talks | Apr 16–17 | Energy, Defense, Airlines, Global macro | Bi-directional (sharp) |\n| TSMC Q1 earnings call | Apr 16 14:00 TPE (02:00 ET) | Semiconductors, AI infra, NVDA/AMD/AVGO/MU | Likely POSITIVE |\n| Pharma tariff comment deadline | Apr 16 | Biotech/Pharma | Potential negative catalyst |\n| Philly Fed / Industrial Production | Apr 17 | Industrials, Macro | Neutral-to-watch |\n\n---\n\n## Summary JSON for Protocol Handoff\n\n```json\n{\n  \"date\": \"2026-04-16\",\n  \"market_sentiment\": {\n    \"fear_greed_index\": 55,\n    \"fear_greed_label\": \"Neutral\",\n    \"vix_current\": 18.15,\n    \"put_call_ratio\": 0.68,\n    \"spy_rsi\": 63.83,\n    \"extreme_sentiment_triggered\": false,\n    \"market_regime\": \"RISK_ON\"\n  },\n  \"top_catalysts\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"C1\",\n      \"title\": \"Iran/US Ceasefire Fragility\",\n      \"impact\": \"NEGATIVE\",\n      \"binary_risk_48h\": true,\n      \"affected_sectors\": [\"Energy\", \"Defense\", \"Airlines\", \"Consumer Discretionary\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"C2\",\n      \"title\": \"Q1 Earnings Beat Wave + TSMC Call Today\",\n      \"impact\": \"POSITIVE\",\n      \"binary_risk_48h\": true,\n      \"affected_sectors\": [\"Financials\", \"Technology\", \"Semiconductors\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"C3\",\n      \"title\": \"100% Pharma Tariffs + China Tariff Threats\",\n      \"impact\": \"NEGATIVE\",\n      \"binary_risk_48h\": true,\n      \"affected_sectors\": [\"Biotech\", \"Pharma\", \"China-exposed Tech\", \"Industrials\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"C4\",\n      \"title\": \"Fed on Hold, FOMC Apr 28-29\",\n      \"impact\": \"NEUTRAL\",\n      \"binary_risk_48h\": false,\n      \"affected_sectors\": [\"Utilities\", \"REITs\", \"Financials\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"C5\",\n      \"title\": \"AI Demand Supercycle / Chip Shortage\",\n      \"impact\": \"POSITIVE\",\n      \"binary_risk_48h\": true,\n      \"affected_sectors\": [\"Semiconductors\", \"Cloud\", \"AI Infrastructure\", \"Networking\"]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"oil_price_wti\": 93.0,\n  \"macro_notes\": \"Iran ceasefire imminently lapsing is the single highest-impact binary risk. AI/semiconductor earnings cycle is the dominant positive structural driver. Pharma tariffs add sector-specific drag. Fed neutral. Overall regime RISK_ON but with elevated geopolitical tail risk.\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\nSources:\n- [CBOE VIX Historical Data - Yahoo Finance](https://finance.yahoo.com/quote/%5EVIX/)\n- [Fear and Greed Index - CNN Markets](https://www.cnn.com/markets/fear-and-greed)\n- [CBOE Daily Market Statistics](https://www.cboe.com/us/options/market_statistics/daily/)\n- [SPY Technical Analysis - Barchart.com](https://www.barchart.com/etfs-funds/quotes/SPY/technical-analysis)\n- [Stock Market Live April 14, 2026 - 24/7 Wall St.](https://247wallst.com/investing/2026/04/14/stock-market-live-april-14-2026-sp-500-spy-wipes-out-iran-losses/)\n- [Trump threatens 50% tariffs on China - CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/04/13/trump-threatens-50percent-tariffs-on-china-as-report-suggests-plans-for-arms-shipment-to-iran.html)\n- [Trump Tariff Rates Could Be Restored by Early July: Bessent - Bloomberg](https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-04-14/trump-tariff-rates-could-be-restored-by-early-july-bessent)\n- [FOMC March 18, 2026 Statement - Federal Reserve](https://www.federalreserve.gov/newsevents/pressreleases/monetary202603